<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586606>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 3. SEM micrographs of two types of conifers from the Early Cretaceous mesofossil flora of Catefica, Portugal. (a) Shoot fragment of Frenelopsis turolensis with terminally short triangular free tips (P0357, sample Catefica 310). (b) Outer surface with papillae and stomata arranged in longitudinal rows (P0357, sample Catefica 310). (c) Stomatal chamber with outer and inner papillae (arrows) (P0357, sample Catefica 310). (d) Flat internode of Pseudofrenelopsis cf. parceramosa (P0132, sample Catefica 315). (e) Outer view of the abaxial surface showing stomatal rows (P0132, sample Catefica 315). (f) Detail of stomatal rows showing massive rings around the stomatal pits (arrows) (P0132, sample Catefica 315). Scale bars = 1 mm (a, d, e); 100 μm (b); 50 μm (f); 5 μm (c)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4586606/files/figure.png" .

